title: Drawing, "Drawings. Studies.  A.  "Cocoa Nut Palm".  B.  "Parasite" winding around a tree trunk.  C. "Small Fan Palm".  Jamaica, West Indies.", June 14, 1865
markings: Stamped in ink, at lower center:  Lugt 457c
inscribed: Inscribed in graphite, at center right: dead leaves / brownish yellow; and at bottom right:  Small Fan Palm / Jamaica June 14th //65 /  Stem below yellowish warm gray with mossy stains / Husks above similar color / with dark brown rubbish
description: Vertical view of a palm tree with two pending big leaves.

tombstone.epitaph:
Drawing, "Drawings. Studies.  A.  "Cocoa Nut Palm".  B.  "Parasite" winding around a tree trunk.  C. "Small Fan Palm".  Jamaica, West Indies.", June 14, 1865.
June 14, 1865. Graphite on cream-colored wove paper. Gift of Louis P. Church. 1917-4-6-c.
